Cops have arrested a 22-year-old man after he shot his ex-girlfriend and allegedly executing her 9-year-old daughter in Texas. Jeremiah Jones was arrested by a SWAT team in Houston on Tuesday. According to the New York Post, he was out on bail at the time of the deadly shooting that killed 9-year-old Khylie Sorrells and injured her mom, Brittany, was booked into the Harris County Jail on counts of capital murder and aggravated assault with a deadly weapon. READ:Â Man in court for allegedly killing ex, daughter! The mum was reportedly watching a movie in bed with Khylie and her two other girls, ages 1 and 7 when Jones showed up at her apartment. She told investigators that Jones, with whom she had broken up two months ago after eight months of dating, demanded that she give him a television that he thought was his. He then ripped the TV off the wall and moved to the living room, where she followed him. As the argument between the pair continued, the man ordered her to hand over her phone. The publication reports that the woman said her ex-boyfriend accused her of seeing another man and became upset when he learned that she had been messaging someone. That is when he ran back into the bedroom where her children were alone and fired two shots, according to investigators. He then allegedly returned to the living room, forced her to get on the floor and shot her in the shoulder, before fleeing in a Chevy Camaro.